<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="88" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,459,522]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,459,485]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males and females of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1907" box="[636,774,459,485]" class="Insecta" family="Vespidae" genus="Cyanotiphia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[636,774,459,485]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Cyanotiphia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by the following combination of characters (after 
<bibRefCitation author="Cameron, P." box="[266,442,495,521]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" pagination="287 - 289" refId="ref2007" refString="Cameron, P. (1907) On the Bornean Tiphiidae, including a new genus. The Entomologist, 40, 287 - 289." type="journal article" year="1907">Cameron, 1907</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Allen, H. W." box="[452,589,495,522]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" pagination="353 - 438" refId="ref1948" refString="Allen, H. W. (1969) Redescriptions of types of Tiphiinae from Asia, Africa, Oceania in the British Museum (NH) and at Oxford University. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 95, 353 - 438. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 26483" type="journal article" year="1969">Allen, 1969</bibRefCitation>
):
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,567,738]" box="[151,680,567,593]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">
1) body colour dark metallic blue (
<figureCitation box="[557,665,567,593]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 2" captionStart-1="FIGURE 3" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox-0="[186,1396,197,1906]" captionTargetBox-1="[164,1430,191,1835]" captionTargetId-0="figure-18@2.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetId-1="figure-19@3.[152,1437,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 2. Cyanotiphia ruficauda, Cameron (male). A. Body in dorsal view. B. Body in ventral view. C. Body in profile view. D. Head in front view. E. Mesosoma in lateral view. F. Mid and hind femora. G. Propodeum dorsal view. T1 and T2. I. T6 and T7. Scale bars: 1 mm." captionText-1="FIGURE 3. Cyanotiphia ruficauda, Cameron (female). A. Body in dorsal view. B. Head in front view. C. Body in ventral view. D. Body in profile view. E. Midtibial spurs. F. Mid and hind femora. G. Forewing. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6637283" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6637285" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6637283/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6637285/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Figs. 2–3</figureCitation>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,567,738]" box="[151,676,603,630]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">
2) presence of two midtibial spurs (
<figureCitation box="[565,663,603,629]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[164,1430,191,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[152,1437,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cyanotiphia ruficauda, Cameron (female). A. Body in dorsal view. B. Head in front view. C. Body in ventral view. D. Body in profile view. E. Midtibial spurs. F. Mid and hind femora. G. Forewing. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6637285" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6637285/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Figs. 3E</figureCitation>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,567,738]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">
3) mid and hind femora,in females, cylindrical, not broadened as in other genera of the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[1212,1318,639,665]" class="Insecta" family="Tiphiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Tiphiinae">Tiphiinae</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1330,1422,639,665]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[164,1430,191,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[152,1437,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cyanotiphia ruficauda, Cameron (female). A. Body in dorsal view. B. Head in front view. C. Body in ventral view. D. Body in profile view. E. Midtibial spurs. F. Mid and hind femora. G. Forewing. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6637285" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6637285/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Figs.3F</figureCitation>
); 4) radius of forewing with an intercubital spur as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Sichel" authorityName="Sichel" box="[751,949,675,701]" class="Insecta" family="Tiphiidae" genus="Paratiphia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[751,872,675,701]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Paratiphia</emphasis>
Sichel
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[964,1064,675,701]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1396,197,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cyanotiphia ruficauda, Cameron (male). A. Body in dorsal view. B. Body in ventral view. C. Body in profile view. D. Head in front view. E. Mesosoma in lateral view. F. Mid and hind femora. G. Propodeum dorsal view. T1 and T2. I. T6 and T7. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6637283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6637283/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Figs. 2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1076,1114,675,701]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[164,1430,191,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[152,1437,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cyanotiphia ruficauda, Cameron (female). A. Body in dorsal view. B. Head in front view. C. Body in ventral view. D. Body in profile view. E. Midtibial spurs. F. Mid and hind femora. G. Forewing. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6637285" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6637285/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">3G</figureCitation>
);
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,567,738]" box="[151,1016,711,738]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">
5) tegulae large, about half the length of pro and mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[861,954,711,737]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[186,1396,197,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Cyanotiphia ruficauda, Cameron (male). A. Body in dorsal view. B. Body in ventral view. C. Body in profile view. D. Head in front view. E. Mesosoma in lateral view. F. Mid and hind femora. G. Propodeum dorsal view. T1 and T2. I. T6 and T7. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6637283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6637283/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Figs.2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[966,1003,711,737]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[164,1430,191,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[152,1437,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Cyanotiphia ruficauda, Cameron (female). A. Body in dorsal view. B. Head in front view. C. Body in ventral view. D. Body in profile view. E. Midtibial spurs. F. Mid and hind femora. G. Forewing. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6637285" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6637285/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">3A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
